{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019e4ZYf1Qz8PRqN9mqfeET1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**What was configured:**\n\n1. **MinIO Service** (`minio`) — The service didn't exist, so the minio-init job had failed and the DNS name `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` wasn't resolving. Created the service exposing port 9000.\n\n2. **`es-secure-settings` Secret** — Created with `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` set to `minioadmin`. Credentials are stored in Kubernetes secrets only, not in `elasticsearch.yml` or environment variables.\n\n3. **Elasticsearch keystore** — Populated the S3 credentials into the keystore on all 5 nodes (es-0, es-1, es-2, es-data-0, es-data-1) using `elasticsearch-keystore add --stdin`.\n\n4. **Secure settings reload** — Called `POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings` to load the keystore entries into the running processes — **no pod restarts required**.\n\n5. **`es-backups` bucket** — Created in MinIO (the minio-init job had failed because the service wasn't yet available).\n\n6. **`minio-repo` repository** — Registered as an S3-type repository pointing at `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000` with path-style access (required for MinIO).\n\n7. **`snapshot-1`** — Created and completed successfully: 3/3 shards, 2 indices (`test-index`, `app-data`), state `SUCCESS`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":542,"cache_read_input_tokens":48389,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":542},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6522192c-11af-4cc3-84de-6ef131c9aa00","uuid":"bceb3052-8956-495f-9a15-e8c0a5eb1a8a","request_id":"req_011CcQUpNputaKtvSS